data.description: Own your own piece of Mount Pleasant Tennessee History. Home is in the Historical Registry! Move In Ready! Originally the "R.B. Cooper House" This 1900 circa home has so much to offer! True Southern Roots surrounds the home from amazing "Rocking Chair" covered Front Porch. With 4 Bedrooms 3 Full Bathrooms (Primary has been completely remodeled and it is gorgeous) there is plenty of room to roam. Home incorporates the best of both Old and New Charm with its original hardwood, 12 FT Ceilings, Circa 1900 10FT Pocket Door, Formal Dining Room, Spacious Kitchen, SS Appliances including a JenAire Oven. Granite countertops.  Butler's Pantry. A large fenced in Back Yard with fruit trees, grape vines and plenty of room for a garden. One of the largest lots on their block of Main Street. There is also a Detached Garage/Shop. Selling As-Is. Cash or Conventional preferred. Must see to appreciate all this home has to offer!
